The paper deals with the computational complexity of voter control in elections, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of algorithms and complexity theory to analyze the problem suggests that it could also fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of machine learning techniques to analyze voting patterns could also place it under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
